DOCUMENT();
loadMacros(
"PG.pl",
"PGbasicmacros.pl",
"PGchoicemacros.pl",
"PGanswermacros.pl",
"PGauxiliaryFunctions.pl",
);
 
TEXT(&beginproblem);
$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

$r = random(2,8,1);
$r1 = $r-1;

BEGIN_TEXT
Find an antiderivative \(G\) of 
\( g(z)=\frac{1}{z^{$r}} \)

$PAR
\(G(z) = \) \{ ans_rule(35) \}

END_TEXT

ANS( fun_cmp( "-(1/($r1*z^($r1)))", 'var'=>['z'], 'mode'=>'antider', 
     	      limits => '[0.01,2]' ) );

$fr = ( $r1 == 1 ) ? '' : "\frac{1}{$r1}";

SOLUTION(EV3(<<'END_SOLUTION'));
$PAR SOLUTION $PAR

We can write \(g(z) = z^{-$r}\).  Then \(g(z) = G'(z)\), so \(G(z)\) must
have the form \(G(z) = -$fr z^{-$r1}\) (or this, plus any
constant). 

END_SOLUTION

ENDDOCUMENT();
